[6], 236, [2] pages (the last page blank), [70] pages of plates : illustrations (some color, some mounted), folded facsimiles, portraits ; 29 cm
"This edition of 975 copies is set in Caslon, Centaur and Cochin types and printed at Whittington on Sommerville Laid, Zerkall mould-made and Americana papers. The colour and duotone plates are printed by CTD Printers, the line blocks are made by Blinford Graphics, and the plates following pp. 24, 40, 98 and 168 are printed by the Aldine Press. 880 copies are bound in stiff covers and 95 copies are quarter-bound in Oasis leather and paper marbled by Colleen Gryspeerdt, and include a separately bound book of wood-engravings for Virgil's Georgics by Edward Craig. Bound by the Fine Bindery and edited by John & Rosalind Randle. July 1994"--Page [4] prelim.
